te a markdown file at docs/red.md with a paragraph about the colour red. Do not ask for confirmation, just make the change.\\\")\\n\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"agent failed: %v\\\", err)\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\n\\t\\ts.Git(t, \\\"add\\\", \\\"docs/\\\")\\n\\t\\ts.Git(t, \\\"commit\\\", \\\"-m\\\", \\\"Add md file about red\\\")\\n\\n\\t\\ttestutil.AssertFileExists(t, s.Dir, \\\"docs/*.md\\\")\\n\\t\\ttestutil.AssertNewCommits(t, s, 1)\\n\\n\\t\\ttestutil.WaitForCheckpoint(t, s, 15*time.Second)\\n\\t\\ttestutil.AssertCheckpointAdvanced(t, s)\\n\\n\\t\\tcpID := testutil.AssertHasCheckpointTrailer(t, s.Dir, \\\"HEAD\\\")\\n\\t\\ttestutil.AssertCheckpointExists(t, s.Dir, cpID)\",\"numLines\":60,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":111}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"7f3676d5-07e3-4979-ad12-cc39d87284f0\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9d081ddb-7eca-4aeb-8c05-837d8e481b94\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"bc17869f-f2b7-4aa6-a08b-802e93c0fc64\",\"version\":\"2.1.58\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/agent-integration-skill\",\"slug\":\"sparkling-skipping-hearth\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01EyzFQCyUzUDhoYaSBnct7r\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I have a complete picture of the new E2E infrastructure. Let me write the updated skill file.\\n\\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\\nThe new E2E infrastructure follows a clean **separation of concerns** pattern:\\n1. `agents/` owns the Agent interface and registration — agents self-register via `init()` + `Register()`, which is the Go idiomatic \\\"plugin\\\" pattern\\n2. `testutil/` provides `ForEachAgent` which combines repo setup, concurrency gating, and timeout scaling into a single higher-order function — eliminating boilerplate from every test\\n3. The `entire/` package wraps CLI invocations so tests never call `exec.Command` directly for the `entire` binary\\n